    "name": "Ryoma",
    "epitet": "Samurai at Ease",
    "display": "Ryoma: Samurai at Ease",
    "description": "High Prince of Hoshido. A font of knowledge about remote and hidden hot springs. Appears in Fire Emblem Fates.",
    "artist": "PenekoR (п猫Ｒ)",
    "voiceActorEN": "Matt Mercer",
    "voiceActorJP": "中村悠一",
    "dialogue": [
        {
            "text": "I am Ryoma, High Prince of Hoshido. I have heard talk of a secluded spring nearby. Would you show me the way?",
            "context": "joined"
        },
        {
            "text": "Make the water as hot as it can get, I say! Battling the heat is a test of fortitude. It is to truly bathe.",
            "context": "castle"
        },
        {
            "text": "In Hoshido, it is quite popular to bathe in a spring in winter. Stepping into the bath as snow falls down around you...there are no words to describe that feeling.",
            "context": "castle"
        },
        {
            "text": "Bathing in this spring won't just heal injuries from battle—it will soothe the fatigue of the day. Join me!",
            "context": "castle"
        },
        {
            "text": "Too hot for you, eh? There are other springs that are a little bit cooler. You ought to find one of those.",
            "context": "castle"
        },
        {
            "text": "When I'm soaking in the bath, I may look relaxed, but I keep my blade in reach. If foes attack, I will be ready.",
            "context": "castle"
        },
        {
            "text": "Please forgive the intrusion. I thought you might like to know of a new hot spring <Friend Name> found.",
            "context": "friend"
        },
        {
            "text": "The power of fresh, hot water!",
            "context": "level"
        },
        {
            "text": "Energy is roiling within me, like the flow of a great spring!",
            "context": "level"
        },
        {
            "text": "The water's a bit tepid today, eh?",
            "context": "level"
        },
        {
            "text": "Heat drives fatigue away. That's what makes a dip in a spring great.",
            "context": "growth"
        },
        {
            "text": "A warrior must never neglect training and always strive for a clear and focused mind. Tension is the enemy of strength. It could cost you dearly, all in a single moment. Training is not just about learning to wield your weapon. It is also about preparing yourself for battle. If you are not ready for the fight when it comes to you, that is your own failure. In my training, the hot spring is an essential tool. It is the support I lean on as I look toward my next fight. I will show you my appreciation for revealing this secluded spring to me when next we fight together.",
            "context": "maxed"
        }
    ],
